From 5fc25acd0365ce9915cfea26985e1ee99dca461f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 16:52:54 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] deps: migrate vm-memory 0.17 -> 0.18.0

Unifies the workspace on vm-memory 0.18.0 (required by the gfxstream
scaffolding, which uses GuestMemoryBackend). In 0.18, GuestMemory's
default methods (get_slice, try_access, find_region, checked_offset,
get_host_address, last_addr, address_in_range) moved to a new
GuestMemoryBackend trait with a blanket impl; callers that imported
only GuestMemory lose access to them. Fixed by importing
GuestMemoryBackend alongside GuestMemory everywhere it's needed, plus
one generic bound update in vsock/packet.rs::get_host_address.

Also enables vm-memory's "rawfd" feature (in vm-memory's own default
features, but stripped by this workspace's default-features = false),
which is required for OwnedFd's WriteVolatile/ReadVolatile impls used
by console/port_io/unix.rs.
